\section{Equity Analysis}
Analysts are interested in valuing a security to assess its merits for inclusion or retention in a portfolio. Analysts use a variety of methods to value a company's equity, including valuation ratios (e.g., the price-to-earnings ratio), discounted cash flow approaches, and residual income approaches (ROE compared to the cost of capital) amongst others. The valuation process has several steps, including: \\
\begin{enumerate}
  \item Understanding the business and the existing financial profile. 
  \item Forecasting company performance.
  \item Selecting the appropriate valuation model.
  \item Converting forecasts to a valuation.
  \item Making the investment decision.
\end{enumerate}
\hfill \\

\subsection{Valuation Ratios}
\hfill \\
